🐟 SmartFishNet – AI for Smarter Fishing

AI-Powered Real-Time Fish Catch Predictor SmartFishNet is an intelligent, real-time fish catch prediction system designed to assist fishermen in
identifying the best fishing zones.
🎯 **Goal**: Predict fish catch quantity and species in real-time using satellite + oceanographic data (depth, SST, salinity, etc.)

IMAGE
---

## 🚨 Problem Statement
PROBLEM STATEMENT
Small-scale fishermen often rely on traditional methods to decide where and when to fish, leading to:

🌊 Wasted fuel and time on unproductive trips
🐠 Overfishing in ecologically fragile zones
💸 Unpredictable income and economic insecurity
⛈️ Safety risks during unstable weather
🛰️ Low adoption of modern technology due to cost/accessibility

SmartFishNet solves this by giving **real-time fish predictions** using **ML + ocean science**!

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```text
┌────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌────────────┐
│ User Input │ --> │ Flask API    │ --> │ ML Models  │
└────────────┘     └────┬─────────┘     └────┬───────┘
                         │                  │
                         │                  ▼
                   Predict Catch       Predict Species
                         │                  │
                         ▼                  ▼
                   JSON Output to Frontend / User

---
#Solution
SmartFishNet provides:

🎯 AI-based prediction of fish species and expected catch volume (kg)
🗺️ Interactive maps showing fishing hotspots
🌤️ Weather and tide alerts for safety
🌐 Works online/offline with minimal bandwidth
🧠 Uses real-world and crowdsourced catch data to train models

## 🚀 Features
- Predict fish species from location + ocean data
- Real-time catch quantity estimation (kg)
- Trained on synthetic + real marine datasets
- API-based backend for integration with mobile/web
- UI ready for fishermen or fishery departments

---

## 🧠 Tech Stack

| Layer       | Tools Used                     |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| ML/AI       | scikit-learn, pandas, numpy    |
| Backend     | Flask or FastAPI               |
| Frontend    | React / HTML-CSS-JS            |
| Deployment  | Streamlit    |
| Data        | Synthetic data + mock fish DB  |

*Mapbox / Leaflet.js for map view
*Axios (for API requests)
